Description: Typical range for industrial cleaning of copper alloys like Aluminum Bronze to ablate contaminants without melting; starting at 200W balances efficiency and safety. Max limited to avoid thermal damage given alloy's ~1040°C melting point. Source: IPG Photonics YLR series specs and studies in Optics and Lasers in Engineering (2018) on metal surface cleaning.
Near-IR wavelength for optimal metal absorption
Beam spot diameter for effective cleaning resolution
Pulse duration for minimal heat-affected zone
Beam travel speed for uniform treatment
Number of cleaning cycles for complete removal
